# 04_resolver_list — first proof of the s187 m2 long-name resolver.
#
# Runs `list` and shows the registry's current contents. After s187 m1
# this is exactly one entry — `tool.node` — because only the Node tool
# button was hand-converted to a curvz::widgets::ToggleButton during
# s186 m2. The six new wrappers (Button, Entry, SpinButton, Scale,
# DropDown, CheckButton) compile in but no construction sites use them
# yet — that's the next session's funnel migration.
#
# After this script runs you should see one line:
#   tool.node
#
# Note: NO "(long_name)" decoration after `tool.node`, because the
# script registry entry "tool.node" is hand-picked and not present in
# widget_names.db. The decoration only appears once widget construction
# sites start registering under the widget_names.db abbrev as their
# scriptable name. That arrives with the funnel migration.
#
# This script is a sanity check, not an assertion-based test — read
# the output by eye.

list
